net.philsprojects.live
Interface Property<T>

Type Parameters:
T - The type of value stored in the property.
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractProperty, PropertyBoolean, PropertyByte, PropertyDouble, PropertyFloat, PropertyGeneric, PropertyInt, PropertyLong, PropertyShort, PropertyString
public interface Property<T>

A property holds a single value used by a strategy implementation. The strategy can either see property changes immediately or an update to the strategy must be invoked for the implementation to see the changes.

Author:
Philip Diffenderfer

Method Detail

getName

java.lang.String getName()
The name of this property, unique in its scope. The typical scope of a property is a strategy, thus all properties in a strategy must be uniquely named.

Returns:
The reference to the name.

getValue

T getValue()
Returns the value of this property. If this property is not immediate this value may not be in use currently until the strategy is updated.

Returns:
The reference to the value.

setValue

T setValue(T newValue)
Sets the value of this property. If this property is immediate the strategy implementation will see it immediately. If this property is not immediate, the strategy will be notified of the change and an update must be invoked for the value set to be seen by its implementation.

Parameters:
newValue - The new value of this property.
Returns:
The previous value of this property, or null if none existed.

hasChanged

boolean hasChanged()
Returns true if this property has been changed it requires the strategy to update for the change to take effect.

Returns:
True if this property has changed and an update is required to apply the changes, otherwise false.

reset

void reset()
Resets this property as unchanged if it is currently not immediate and has been changed since the last strategy update.

isImmediate

boolean isImmediate()
Returns whether changes to this property are seen immediately by the strategy implementation or the strategy must be updated for changes to be applied.

Returns:
True if the strategy implementation sees changes to this property immediately or false if the strategy must be updated for the property changes to be applied to the implementation.

getValidator

Returns the validator of property changes.

Returns:
The reference to the property change validator.

setValidator

void setValidator(PropertyValidator<T> validator)
Sets the property change validator.

Parameters:
validator - The new property validator.

getListeners

Notifier<PropertyListener<T>> getListeners()
Returns the notifier which manages the listeners to changes in the property. PropertyListeners can be directly added and removed to the notifier. Avoid invoking the methods of the proxy object in the notifier since it may notify the listeners falsely when a change has not actually occurred with the property.

Returns:
The reference to the PropertyListener notifier.
